{"questionId":"17527","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = {x^4} - 54{x^2} + 60x\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>54</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>60</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>, for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 1 \\leqslant x \\leqslant 6\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;The following diagram shows the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e2818b3d7e5319794cf66f907e9004290f1e196a.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">There are <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>-intercepts at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 0\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> and at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = p\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>. There is a maximum at point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = a\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>, and a point of inflexion at point <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{B}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = b\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R\"> <mi>R</mi> </math></span> be the region enclosed by the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span>, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>-axis and the lines <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = p\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>p</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = b\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>b</mi> </math></span>. The region <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R\"> <mi>R</mi> </math></span> is rotated 360º about the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>-axis. Find the volume of&nbsp;the solid formed.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute <strong>either their</strong> limits <strong>or</strong> the function into volume formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int_{1.14}^3 {{f^2}} \"> <msubsup> <mo>∫</mo> <mrow> <mn>1.14</mn> </mrow> <mn>3</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi \\int {{{\\left( {{x^4} - 54{x^2} + 60x} \\right)}^2}} {\\text{d}}x\"> <mi>π</mi> 